metadata.name: Mustachioed #170
metadata.description:
Who has the chance to have a weird mustache on his face?
Art, personality, politics, religion, power or any other factor has made some mustache models dependent on individuals and takes its name from its first or most famous owner.
Mustachioed is a historical research that aims to link the history of the mustache to the digital world.
Each piece of mustachioed is a ticket to enter this unique world where different samples of mustaches are collected.
Who has the chance to register an outstanding mustache to their names?
We must wait and see.
This research will continue!

Collection of unique men with weird mustaches. Including 13 traits and 473 Attributes.

metadata.name: Metal Waves #32
metadata.description:
The generative arts help us to make the hardest metals and shape them to our liking. When large objects are broken into smaller pieces, flexibility increases, and the smaller the pieces, the more creative you become.
This work comprises thousend of lines made up of hundreds of points arranged in the same direction, waves made up of thousands of lines, and pieces made of dozens of waves.
Considering all the starting and ending points of these waves on the circumference of a circle is perhaps the most challenging part, In order to yield something like a round art board.

You can order a piece in any size and color if you are one of the owners. On Twitter, DM your custom size and colors.

metadata.name: Less is More #43
metadata.description:
In this case, we tried to avoid abstract expressionist tendencies by removing personal scenarios.
Take a step back and let's create a geometrical work that intentionally avoids the usual conventional elements, focusing mainly on logic and physics concepts such as mathematical expansions and gravity.
In fact, we based our work and expression on the basis of simplicity and simple methods, as well as free from the usual philosophical or pseudo-philosophical complexity, and we concluded that by using simple geometric shapes, color, form, and material can be achieved in a pure manner.

metadata.name: Magic Blocks #9
metadata.description:
Different patterns are combined in multiple groups based on harmony in the main blocks.
A random coordinate system is used to place these colored blocks.
Each block uses a quadruple color palette, with one color for the background and two colors randomly selected from the three main colors.
A shadow is a block of black and white that exists in different patterns.
In three different modes, these blocks can be viewed:
-Colorless and textureless blocks
-Textured blocks without backgrounds
-Backgrounds and textures for blocks
The shadow blocks can be made up of just one specific pattern, with different dimensions, or they can be made up of several patterns, all with different dimensions.

metadata.name: Cube on Cube #9
metadata.description:
This token generates a plottable SVG file, a different arrangement of cubes.
The cubes are designed in 2D view, then placed next to each other or on top of each other in eight different directions. The goal is to challenge the audience's mind to discover the holes or protrusions produced by placing the cubes together.
To produce random parts made of cubes, those in the same direction are merged together, which is a turning point in this project.
Do you need a different output from your piece?  Then use controllers!

Controllers 
G - Change light direction
F - Add/remove frame
L - Add/remove base lines
D - Change base lines direction
R - Reset to default settings
P - Save as PNG
S - Export high resolution SVG

Note : When you have a piece with many shapes, controllers may run delayed. (Depending on your device).

Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Mandala #12
metadata.description:
A mandala is a geometric configuration of symbols.
With the help of vectors, the symmetrical geometric shapes of the mandala automatically attract the attention of the person to the center of the circle.
Most artists today draw mandalas without circles and squares, which is amazing from an aesthetic standpoint, but an original mandala with the characteristics that are present in the historical and ancient definitions will definitely have circles and squares.
Mandalas are seen by Carl Jung as archetypes of the self, symbols of wholeness and order, which are used to organize and rearrange chaos.
The mandala design is a way to relieve tension and focus the mind.
Mandalas are used in art therapy to help patients gain mastery over their minds and achieve peace, also Mandala establishes a new connection between the conscious and the unconscious.
This old pattern throws out internal issues and acts as a projection device.

Everyone in the world has their own mandala that can be formed in their paintings and artistic activities.

metadata.name: Silent Marsh #32
metadata.description:
Naturalism is the only art school faithful to nature among the visual arts. Including a descriptive painting of nature and minimally altered human figures.
The fidelity to nature gives the piece a photographic feel.
Like other painting schools, this style was heavily influenced by the (aesthetics) and (culture) of different regions.
Here, the only question is:
Is it possible for a painting to be completely naturalistic without the artist creating and reflecting his thoughts?

This collection represents our mental image of nature, which is implemented by code.
